  • Without assignment, deletion wont change original vectors

V9: Subsetting by logic comparisons

  • two methods to filter data from vectors, by index vector or a logical vector with equal length.
a <- seq(11, 55, 11)
a[c(T, F, T, F, T)]
## [1] 11 33 55
a[a%%2==1]
## [1] 11 33 55
a%%2
## [1] 1 0 1 0 1
a%%2==1
## [1]  TRUE FALSE  TRUE FALSE  TRUE
a <- c("","","","")
a[nchar(a)>3]
## [1] ""   ""
# which will return "index-of"
a <- seq(11, 55, 11)
a[which(a%%2==1)]
## [1] 11 33 55
which(a%%2==1)
## [1] 1 3 5

V10: Sorting

x <- c(33, 55, 22, 13, 4, 24)

# Sort it directly
sort(x)
## [1]  4 13 22 24 33 55
# Get the order
order(x) # 5, 4, 3, 6, 1, 2 <- the min to max sequence of original index
## [1] 5 4 3 6 1 2
x[order(x)] # will produce identical vector with sort(x)
## [1]  4 13 22 24 33 55
# assign to replace x
x <- sort(x)
